00:29:25,521 --> 00:29:26,001
Let's go.

569
00:29:40,641 --> 00:29:43,441
Does it hurt? Why is it so swollen?

570
00:29:47,761 --> 00:29:48,761
Can you be a bit gentler?

571
00:29:49,601 --> 00:29:52,281
You're a grown man, can't handle a little pain?

572
00:29:53,121 --> 00:29:55,401
With your strength, a minor injury feels serious.

573
00:29:58,841 --> 00:30:00,081
Does every guy who kisses you

574
00:30:00,121 --> 00:30:01,001
get slapped by you?

575
00:30:01,441 --> 00:30:02,281
Who would dare kiss you then?

576
00:30:03,761 --> 00:30:05,081
And you blame me for that?

577
00:30:05,121 --> 00:30:06,601
You didn't warn me beforehand.

578
00:30:07,521 --> 00:30:08,121
So I...

579
00:30:08,561 --> 00:30:10,281
That's just my first reaction.

580
00:30:12,561 --> 00:30:14,401
Do TV drama leads announce before kissing?

581
00:30:14,441 --> 00:30:15,401
Do they give a heads-up?

582
00:30:15,441 --> 00:30:16,801
They follow the script.

583
00:30:19,801 --> 00:30:21,201
You haven't kissed in ages, have you?

584
00:30:21,561 --> 00:30:22,641
Your kissing skills are so awkward.

585
00:30:23,241 --> 00:30:25,441
Here's a tip: practice more.

586
00:30:26,561 --> 00:30:27,521
Kissing isn't something

587
00:30:27,561 --> 00:30:28,801
you can just practice with anyone.

588
00:30:28,841 --> 00:30:29,761
You think I'm like you?

589
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:30,961
Hey, wait.

590
00:30:33,361 --> 00:30:34,281
Just reminding you,

591
00:30:34,321 --> 00:30:35,441
you owe me a favor.

592
00:30:35,481 --> 00:30:36,161
Don't try to skip out.

593
00:30:37,401 --> 00:30:38,681
Relax, I know.

594
00:30:52,521 --> 00:30:52,801
Don't move.

595
00:30:54,121 --> 00:30:54,801
Hold still.

596
00:30:55,041 --> 00:30:55,921
Very good, very good.

597
00:31:06,081 --> 00:31:07,441
See, photos speak for themselves.

598
00:31:15,361 --> 00:31:16,641
Don't keep things bottled up.

599
00:31:16,881 --> 00:31:17,521
Talk to me.

600
00:31:20,641 --> 00:31:22,081
You're overthinking.

601
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:25,041
I don't have anything bottled up.

602
00:31:25,761 --> 00:31:26,761
There's no one else here.

603
00:31:27,961 --> 00:31:30,121
I'll forget all this by tomorrow.

604
00:31:32,641 --> 00:31:34,001
Actually...

605
00:31:34,601 --> 00:31:36,401
Every time I visit Grandma,

606
00:31:38,401 --> 00:31:40,161
I really miss my parents.

607
00:31:41,921 --> 00:31:42,761
So...

608
00:31:42,801 --> 00:31:44,761
That's why you come here to watch the stars.

609
00:31:48,801 --> 00:31:51,721
Watching stars calms me down.

610
00:31:55,161 --> 00:31:56,601
Look at these stars in the sky,

611
00:31:58,401 --> 00:31:59,801
they seem lonely too.

612
00:32:01,921 --> 00:32:04,561
But they keep shining.

613
00:32:06,441 --> 00:32:07,121
You know,

614
00:32:07,841 --> 00:32:10,081
I loved shooting starry skies in college.

615
00:32:11,761 --> 00:32:13,441
Because a girl once told me,

616
00:32:14,081 --> 00:32:15,601
when your loved ones leave you,

617
00:32:16,001 --> 00:32:17,041
they become stars.

618
00:32:18,761 --> 00:32:20,281
Whenever you look up at the night sky,

619
00:32:21,761 --> 00:32:24,041
they're the brightest one up there.

620
00:32:26,761 --> 00:32:27,441
Hey...

621
00:32:27,481 --> 00:32:29,361
I'm not saying this to make you cry.

622
00:32:29,681 --> 00:32:30,481
Please don't cry.

623
00:32:32,321 --> 00:32:34,161
You're really bad at comforting girls.

624
00:32:34,201 --> 00:32:34,921
You know,

625
00:32:38,321 --> 00:32:39,841
so that girl you mentioned

626
00:32:41,761 --> 00:32:43,081
must've meant a lot to you, right?

627
00:32:43,801 --> 00:32:45,761
Otherwise, you wouldn't still remember.

628
00:32:47,881 --> 00:32:48,561
She...

629
00:32:49,841 --> 00:32:50,761
was my ex-girlfriend.

630
00:32:54,441 --> 00:32:56,241
So every time I shoot the stars,

631
00:32:57,481 --> 00:32:58,121
I think of her.

632
00:33:00,481 --> 00:33:01,921
But it's not that kind of longing.

633
00:33:02,481 --> 00:33:04,881
She must be doing well now.

634
00:33:08,321 --> 00:33:10,481
Your ex was a photographer too?

635
00:33:13,681 --> 00:33:15,041
We met through photography.

636
00:33:16,001 --> 00:33:17,161
And parted because of it.

637
00:33:18,481 --> 00:33:19,361
Pretty ironic, huh?

638
00:33:23,921 --> 00:33:24,281
Hey...

639
00:33:25,001 --> 00:33:26,641
Everything I'm telling you now,

640
00:33:26,681 --> 00:33:28,041
you'll forget by tomorrow morning.

641
00:33:29,201 --> 00:33:29,761
Alright.

642
00:33:29,801 --> 00:33:31,721
Let's stop talking about sad things.

643
00:33:32,721 --> 00:33:33,841
How about we grab a drink?

644
00:33:34,601 --> 00:33:35,081
Tea.

645
00:33:35,641 --> 00:33:36,001
Let's go.

646
00:33:50,441 --> 00:33:51,321
That Su Wen guy...

647
00:33:52,561 --> 00:33:54,801
is probably monopolizing Yao Yuan, talking nonstop.

648
00:33:55,441 --> 00:33:56,601
One minute it's secrets,

649
00:33:56,641 --> 00:33:58,441
the next it's pre-wedding talk.

650
00:34:13,641 --> 00:34:14,361
Brother Anlan.

651
00:34:16,921 --> 00:34:18,121
Are you working overtime?

652
00:34:18,161 --> 00:34:19,081
I thought you never worked late.

653
00:34:20,081 --> 00:34:22,041
If I don't finish my work,

654
00:34:22,561 --> 00:34:23,721
I'll just

655
00:34:24,281 --> 00:34:26,401
start overthinking.

656
00:34:26,441 --> 00:34:28,041
It's something important.

657
00:34:28,081 --> 00:34:29,561
I have to finish it today. Why are you here?

658
00:34:30,041 --> 00:34:31,321
I brought you something to drink.

659
00:34:32,401 --> 00:34:33,401
Brother Anlan.

660
00:34:34,121 --> 00:34:34,721
When you're done,

661
00:34:34,761 --> 00:34:36,041
let's go out together, okay?

662
00:34:36,601 --> 00:34:37,321
I invited a bunch of friends.

663
00:34:37,361 --> 00:34:38,041
I'm not going.

664
00:34:39,321 --> 00:34:40,161
Come on, please?

665
00:34:40,201 --> 00:34:41,401
I said I'm not going.

666
00:34:47,801 --> 00:34:49,081
Why are you always so harsh to me?

667
00:34:49,961 --> 00:34:51,241
You're only gentle with Sister Yao.

668
00:34:52,121 --> 00:34:53,201
That's really unfair.

669
00:35:36,121 --> 00:35:36,961
Yo, yo, yo.

670
00:35:37,761 --> 00:35:40,041
Our relationship expert, Master Wen,

671
00:35:40,681 --> 00:35:42,361
even hits a wall sometimes.

672
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,040
It's my first time meeting someone like Yao Xinran,

673
00:35:47,081 --> 00:35:48,281
who's immune to both soft and hard approaches.

674
00:35:48,321 --> 00:35:49,241
And she throws in an iron palm, too.

675
00:35:50,881 --> 00:35:53,441
Maybe that's just her being flustered.

676
00:35:54,121 --> 00:35:57,081
Don't you always say a reaction means feelings?

677
00:35:57,881 --> 00:36:00,401
It's silence that's the real worry.

678
00:36:02,321 --> 00:36:03,881
Here's to you growing wisdom in love.

679
00:36:04,481 --> 00:36:05,081
Let me ask you then,

680
00:36:05,921 --> 00:36:08,481
how do you checkmate Yao Xinran in this game?

681
00:36:10,521 --> 00:36:12,321
Didn't Sun Tzu say it best?

682
00:36:13,401 --> 00:36:15,641
Surprise is the highest strategy.

683
00:36:17,201 --> 00:36:18,241
If I were you,

684
00:36:19,041 --> 00:36:20,521
I'd weave myself into her life.

685
00:36:21,281 --> 00:36:23,961
Make her unable to be without me.

686
00:36:25,521 --> 00:36:26,801
By your logic,

687
00:36:26,841 --> 00:36:28,161
you spend every day with Jiang Anlan,

688
00:36:28,201 --> 00:36:29,321
together twenty-four hours a day.

689
00:36:30,041 --> 00:36:31,761
Wouldn't that spark a romance?

690
00:36:32,121 --> 00:36:32,681
Absolutely not.

691
00:36:33,201 --> 00:36:35,161
Are you crazy? No way.

692
00:36:36,601 --> 00:36:38,161
You run around for him all day.

693
00:36:38,641 --> 00:36:40,481
Where else can you find such a reliable partner?

694
00:36:40,961 --> 00:36:42,481
Too bad you're the same gender.

695
00:36:42,521 --> 00:36:44,481
Otherwise, I'd totally root for you.

696
00:36:45,641 --> 00:36:47,241
Even if I look for a partner,

697
00:36:47,601 --> 00:36:49,761
I wouldn't pick a boss who's an iceberg.

698
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:52,801
I want someone witty and funny.

699
00:36:52,841 --> 00:36:53,961
That's my type.

700
00:36:54,641 --> 00:36:56,361
So if I were a girl,

701
00:36:56,401 --> 00:36:58,041
you'd be my ideal match, right?

702
00:36:58,881 --> 00:37:00,081
Overflowing with confidence.

703
00:37:00,401 --> 00:37:02,441
Why not use that on Yao Xinran?

704
00:37:05,281 --> 00:37:06,081
If it were that easy,

705
00:37:06,121 --> 00:37:07,441
would I still be struggling here?

706
00:37:08,921 --> 00:37:09,561
So,

707
00:37:10,601 --> 00:37:12,641
our love expert Master Wen,

708
00:37:13,121 --> 00:37:14,161
your radar's not working?

709
00:37:20,281 --> 00:37:21,001
Honestly,

710
00:37:21,641 --> 00:37:22,721
I don't know how I feel about her.

711
00:37:23,321 --> 00:37:24,841
When I see her, I just want to tease her.

712
00:37:25,601 --> 00:37:27,561
She's especially cute when she's mad.

713
00:37:28,321 --> 00:37:29,161
Anyway,

714
00:37:32,321 --> 00:37:33,441
I can't really explain it.

715
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:34,600
I've never felt this way before.

716
00:37:36,081 --> 00:37:39,041
Wow, Master Wen has met his match.

717
00:37:40,401 --> 00:37:42,601
Didn't you say your new book lacks material?

718
00:37:43,001 --> 00:37:44,161
Just write this in.

719
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:46,480
It'll definitely catch readers' attention.

720
00:37:47,041 --> 00:37:49,161
After all, everyone has a crush phase.

721
00:37:49,201 --> 00:37:50,041
Everyone goes through it.

722
00:37:50,681 --> 00:37:52,081
Even if it lasts a long time,

723
00:37:52,121 --> 00:37:53,081
it might not lead anywhere.

724
00:37:53,601 --> 00:37:54,201
Don't you think?

725
00:37:56,961 --> 00:37:58,121
Finally, you sound human.

726
00:37:58,161 --> 00:38:00,321
Write down all this drama, fill up the pages.

727
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:02,281
Tonight, it's on me.

728
00:38:02,321 --> 00:38:04,041
Come on, cheers to you.

729
00:38:17,321 --> 00:38:19,481
Didn't you say you'd stay overnight?

730
00:38:21,401 --> 00:38:24,081
You clearly said you wanted to stay longer.

731
00:38:26,201 --> 00:38:27,361
Something came up tomorrow.

732
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:30,120
You're worried someone might overthink, right?

733
00:38:33,321 --> 00:38:33,841
Yao Yuan,

734
00:38:36,481 --> 00:38:37,041
come here.

735
00:38:37,761 --> 00:38:39,921
Grandma packed this bag for you.

736
00:38:39,961 --> 00:38:41,241
It's full of your favorite foods.

737
00:38:41,681 --> 00:38:44,041
Red bean buns and green bean paste.

738
00:38:44,561 --> 00:38:45,521
And a chicken.

739
00:38:46,001 --> 00:38:47,121
This chicken,

740
00:38:47,161 --> 00:38:48,761
Grandma picked it just for you.

741
00:38:49,321 --> 00:38:51,161
Take it home and make soup.

742
00:38:51,201 --> 00:38:52,961
It's really good for your health.

743
00:38:53,841 --> 00:38:55,201
And these two bundles of greens.

744
00:38:55,561 --> 00:38:57,241
Look how fresh they are.

745
00:38:57,281 --> 00:38:58,241
No pesticides at all.

746
00:38:58,521 --> 00:38:59,481
Grandma picked them herself.

747
00:38:59,521 --> 00:39:00,841
She picked them just this morning.

748
00:39:01,481 --> 00:39:02,241
Grandma,

749
00:39:02,281 --> 00:39:04,121
this is too much, I can't finish it all.

750
00:39:06,641 --> 00:39:07,521
Yeah,

751
00:39:08,081 --> 00:39:09,761
I should've packed less.

752
00:39:10,201 --> 00:39:11,001
But this way,

753
00:39:11,841 --> 00:39:13,081
when you finish it,

754
00:39:14,401 --> 00:39:15,961
you'll come back soon.

755
00:39:16,921 --> 00:39:18,521
Grandma,

756
00:39:18,561 --> 00:39:20,401
I'll visit whenever I have time, okay?

757
00:39:21,081 --> 00:39:21,561
Alright.

758
00:39:23,081 --> 00:39:24,441
Grandma,

759
00:39:24,481 --> 00:39:26,321
Maybe next time we come back,

760
00:39:26,361 --> 00:39:27,201
we'll bring wedding candies.

761
00:39:28,161 --> 00:39:29,481
Oh, that would be wonderful!

762
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:31,280
Don't listen to his nonsense.

763
00:39:31,321 --> 00:39:32,561
We're just friends.

764
00:39:33,681 --> 00:39:34,121
Grandma,

765
00:39:35,161 --> 00:39:36,241
we're

766
00:39:36,281 --> 00:39:38,081
more than colleagues,

767
00:39:38,121 --> 00:39:39,601
less than lovers.

768
00:39:40,481 --> 00:39:42,001
What are you talking about?

769
00:39:44,441 --> 00:39:46,121
The car's almost here, let's go.

770
00:39:46,161 --> 00:39:47,161
Grandma, we're leaving now.

771
00:39:47,201 --> 00:39:49,321
Alright, be careful on the road.

772
00:39:55,161 --> 00:39:56,281
What's wrong with this light?

773
00:39:57,121 --> 00:39:57,881
Grandma, this light—

774
00:39:57,921 --> 00:39:59,281
You haven't changed it in ages.

775
00:40:00,281 --> 00:40:03,761
It's fine, as long as it works.

776
00:40:04,081 --> 00:40:04,921
No way.

777
00:40:04,961 --> 00:40:06,521
It's broken, and we're here now.

778
00:40:06,561 --> 00:40:07,561
If I weren't here,

779
00:40:07,601 --> 00:40:08,921
how would you change it alone?

780
00:40:08,961 --> 00:40:10,241
What if you got hurt?

781
00:40:10,281 --> 00:40:11,201
It's fine, it's fine.

782
00:40:12,361 --> 00:40:13,881
Grandma, since I'm here today,

783
00:40:13,921 --> 00:40:14,481
let me change it for you.

784
00:40:16,361 --> 00:40:17,601
Alright then, come on.

785
00:40:19,201 --> 00:40:20,601
Here, the bulb.

786
00:40:20,641 --> 00:40:21,201
Go slow, okay?

787
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:21,560
Okay.

788
00:40:23,801 --> 00:40:24,321
Be careful.

789
00:40:25,201 --> 00:40:26,401
What's wrong with this table?

790
00:40:27,881 --> 00:40:28,841
Grandma,

791
00:40:29,601 --> 00:40:30,401
Grandma,

792
00:40:31,641 --> 00:40:32,641
The money I asked Uncle to give you—

793
00:40:32,681 --> 00:40:33,721
is it not enough?

794
00:40:36,081 --> 00:40:36,681
It's fine.

795
00:40:37,041 --> 00:40:38,841
If it's not enough, I'll give you more.

796
00:40:39,321 --> 00:40:40,521
Oh, no need, no need.

797
00:40:40,561 --> 00:40:42,041
Grandma has enough for herself.

798
00:40:43,321 --> 00:40:44,241
Really, it's enough.

799
00:40:44,281 --> 00:40:45,961
Grandma, you have to take it.

800
00:40:46,361 --> 00:40:48,041
Grandma, just accept it.

801
00:40:48,081 --> 00:40:49,721
If you don't, Yao Yuan can't sleep.

802
00:40:49,881 --> 00:40:50,601
Please, just take it.

803
00:40:51,441 --> 00:40:52,801
If it's not enough, ask me for more.

804
00:40:53,121 --> 00:40:53,721
Alright then.

805
00:40:55,121 --> 00:40:56,801
Did I give Uncle too little money?

806
00:40:58,041 --> 00:40:58,841
It's fine, it's fine.

807
00:41:04,001 --> 00:41:04,761
Grandma, the lightbulb.

808
00:41:04,801 --> 00:41:05,521
Thanks to you.

809
00:41:06,761 --> 00:41:07,481
Let's go.

810
00:41:10,521 --> 00:41:11,361
Is everything installed?

811
00:41:12,081 --> 00:41:13,161
Be careful on the road.

812
00:41:13,201 --> 00:41:14,401
We're leaving now, Grandma.

813
00:41:15,521 --> 00:41:16,681
Take care of yourself.

814
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,680
The table's been changed.

815
00:41:18,401 --> 00:41:19,201
Grandma, we're heading out.

816
00:41:19,240 --> 00:41:19,760
Okay.

817
00:41:20,041 --> 00:41:20,721
Go slowly.

818
00:41:21,801 --> 00:41:22,881
Make sure to look after yourself.

819
00:41:22,921 --> 00:41:23,281
Hey.

820
00:41:23,481 --> 00:41:24,401
Grandma, you don't need to see us off.

821
00:41:26,081 --> 00:41:27,481
We'll visit you again when we have time.

822
00:41:27,641 --> 00:41:28,041
Okay.

823
00:41:28,521 --> 00:41:29,321
Grandma, bye-bye.

824
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:30,320
Goodbye.

825
00:41:30,561 --> 00:41:31,281
Goodbye, Grandma.
